From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Loopy floor-console spike <to.sasovsky@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: don't abort plane assignment on unplaceable views (RPi4)

On the Raspberry Pi 4 (vc4 / V3D KMS), drm_output_find_plane_for_view()
aborts the whole compositor the moment a Wayland or Xwayland client sets
a pointer cursor: a view reaches the plane-candidate switch with a NULL
framebuffer (or a non-shm cursor buffer) and trips one of the asserts in
backend-drm/state-propose.c. The crash takes the kiosk app down on every
mouse movement.

The asserts encode "this can't happen" invariants that the vc4 cursor /
overlay plane path violates. Turn them into graceful `continue`s: an
incompatible view simply skips that hardware plane and falls through to
GL renderer compositing (weston's normal fallback), so the pointer no
longer crashes the compositor and the cursor stays visible.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [hardware/config-specific workaround]

---
 libweston/backend-drm/state-propose.c | 12 ++++++++----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libweston/backend-drm/state-propose.c b/libweston/backend-drm/state-propose.c
index 1e62e2b..d5e89cb 100644
--- a/libweston/backend-drm/state-propose.c
+++ b/libweston/backend-drm/state-propose.c
@@ -517,11 +517,13 @@ drm_output_find_plane_for_view(struct drm_output_state *state,

 		switch (plane->type) {
 		case WDRM_PLANE_TYPE_CURSOR:
-			assert(buffer->shm_buffer);
+			if (!buffer->shm_buffer)
+				continue;
 			assert(plane == output->cursor_plane);
 			break;
 		case WDRM_PLANE_TYPE_PRIMARY:
-			assert(fb);
+			if (!fb)
+				continue;
 			if (plane != output->scanout_plane)
 				continue;
 			if (mode != DRM_OUTPUT_PROPOSE_STATE_PLANES_ONLY)
@@ -530,8 +532,10 @@ drm_output_find_plane_for_view(struct drm_output_state *state,
 				continue;
 			break;
 		case WDRM_PLANE_TYPE_OVERLAY:
-			assert(fb);
-			assert(mode != DRM_OUTPUT_PROPOSE_STATE_RENDERER_ONLY);
+			if (!fb)
+				continue;
+			if (mode == DRM_OUTPUT_PROPOSE_STATE_RENDERER_ONLY)
+				continue;
 			/* if the view covers the whole output, put it in the
 			 * scanout plane, not overlay */
 			if (view_matches_entire_output &&
